news.title: Kolkata civic body set to amend law to deal with illegal buildings
news.para: A stricter law, said a KMC buildings department official, would help the civic body prosecute and jail unscrupulous builders for a longer time for not only going ahead with constructions without seeking civic sanction but also using inferior materials, endangering public safety.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body, GMC to get infra cess share directly into accounts
news.para: Infrastructure cess — a 2% charge collected as a part of stamp duty on the sale and purchase of new property — is collected by the state govt and released to ULBs and development authorities in instalments.

news.title: Cognizant puts headquarter in Chennai up for sale, eyes Rs 800 crore
news.para: Cognizant is putting its 15-acre India headquarters in Chennai, featuring a 4 lakh sq ft office space, up for sale, with estimates suggesting it could fetch Rs 750-800 crore. Managed by JLL, the sale is part of a consolidation of operations in Chennai, aiming for completion by December 2024.

news.title: ED attaches 401.65 acre lands worth Rs 834.03 crore of Emaar India & MGF Developments
news.para: Among these attached properties, EMAAR India Ltd's assets are valued at approximately Rs 501.13 crore, while MGF Developments Ltd's assets are valued at around Rs 332.69 crore.

news.title: SC nod for purchasable FAR, to allow 13,000 more Amrapali flats to come up
news.para: All parties, including Noida and Greater Noida authorities, NBCC, and homebuyers, have agreed to the purchasable floor area ratio, aiding the completion of pending projects and repayment of debts.

news.title: Construction of Dharavi redevelopment to start in 6-8 months: SVR Srinivas, CEO, DRP
news.para: The Dharavi Redevelopment Project, covering nearly 600 acres in Mumbai, will start in 6-8 months. A survey for eligibility will end by March. Adani Group and the Government of Maharashtra lead the project. It's a joint venture poised to rehabilitate residents of Dharavi, aiming to reimagine one of the largest informal settlements.

news.title: Noida DM tells builders to clear dues and expedite registry of flats
news.para: From Feb 26 to Aug 29, 2024, a total of 7,368 flats were registered in GB Nagar. Of these, 5,297 flats were registered under rehabilitation schemes, while the remaining 2,070 flats were registered through the routine process.

news.title: Maharashtra government to consider stamp duty concession on property registration
news.para: Atul Save, Minister of Housing, Government of Maharashtra, said it would consider the real estate developers' demand of granting further concessions in registration and stamp duty.

news.title: Macrotech Developers acquires Opexefi Services & One Box Warehouse for Rs 95.76 crore
news.para: While Opexefi Services has been acquired for Rs 46.67 crore, One Box Warehouse has been acquired for Rs 49.09 crore.

news.title: Trehan IRIS to manage Marriott International's hotel in Greater Noida
news.para: In 2022, Trehan IRIS had announced an investment of around Rs 400 crore to develop this commercial project, comprising retail and office spaces as well as a hotel, in Greater Noida.

news.title: Suraksha Group earmarks 2,552 acre of land for Jaypee Infratech lenders in Delhi-NCR
news.para: Suraksha Group has taken control of Jaypee Infratech Ltd, allocating 2,552 acres of land for lenders. The group is focusing on completing 20,000 pending flats in Delhi-NCR. They have invested Rs 125 crore as equity and arranged a Rs 3,000 crore loan. Construction on several stalled towers has resumed.

news.title: Betting on Chinese demand, Hong Kong developers turn to rental market
news.para: Rents of private homes in Hong Kong in July rose to their highest level in nearly five years, while home prices dropped 22% during the same period, latest data showed on Wednesday.

news.title: Industry came forward for regulations on small & medium REITs: Sebi chief
news.para: Recently Sebi implemented regulations for small and medium real estate investment trusts (SM REITs) aimed at significantly increasing investor interest in fractional ownership of real estate assets.

news.title: Housing sales value in Mumbai region may cross Rs 1.35 lakh crore in 2024: Report
news.para: "As of June 2024, Mumbai stands as one of the leading contributors to pan-India launches and sales. Residential sales value in 2023 breached Rs 1 lakh crore and is expected to surpass Rs 1.35 lakh crore in 2024, setting a record high for the city," JLL said in a statement.

news.title: Urban Vault leases one lakh sq ft office space in Brigade Summit in Bengaluru
news.para: The company has a big presence in Bengaluru and it is all set to enter Pune, Gurugram and Hyderabad market by the end of this fiscal. Its occupancy level in the operational centres stands at 91 per cent.

news.title: BCD Group appoints Ashwinder R. Singh as vice chairman and CEO
news.para: The current managing director, Angad Singh Bedi has been elevated to chairman and managing director.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh to become best energy efficient state: CM
news.para: On Tuesday, CM Chandrababu Naidu held a meeting with EESL CEO Vishal Kapoor and representatives of the company at the Secretariat to discuss ways to increase energy efficiency in the state.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body releases list of top 100 property tax defaulters
news.para: ​​Notable defaulters on the list include Bengaluru Metropolitan Transport Corporation, Karnataka State Road Transport Corporation, Bengaluru Metropolitan Rail Corporation Limited, the Transport Department, and the Karnataka Housing Board, among others.

news.title: Delhi: Vasant Kunj residents protest against new housing complex
news.para: Rohit Sejwal, a representative of the housing project, however, claimed that all necessary permissions had been acquired and there was no violation of regulations.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad development body to crack down on illegal layouts
news.para: According to sources, many builders who received initial approval from Huda to develop layouts failed to obtain the necessary Development Completion Certificates (CC) but proceeded to sell plots without them.
